e depth of King's political-theological critique of police violence as the illegitimate appropriation of the racialized state of exception. As Thompson argues, it is in part through its appropriation of German philosophy and theology that King's ontology condemns the perpetual American state of racial exception that permits unlimited police violence against Black lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAfrican American philosophy. 0aAfrican AmericansxCivil rights. 0aNonviolencexPhilosophy. 0aOntology. 0aPhilosophy, German. 0aRacexPhilosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh  aAfrican American philosophy.  aBlack power.  aGerman philosophy.  aNonviolence.  acivil rights.  agnosticism.  aontology.  apolice violence.  apolitical theology.  atheology.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503632080423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503632080/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles